    "summary": "Marijn Goes is a team leader for Chemistry and Physics at NWO (Dutch Research Council), leading an enthousistic team of 14 policy officers and program coordinators. in addition to that he is science-secretary to the Topsector Chemistry - the national coordinating body on Public-private partnerships in Chemistry  Before this he used to co\u00f6rdinate international cooperations in the Science Domain of NWO. Also he has fullfilled the position of corporate secretary at  ChemistryNL (Topsector)\nBefore his career at NWO Marijn was R&D director for the International Technology Centre for Colour and Colourants in PPG coatings (architectural, protective and marine coatings) leading 5 teams of professionals (30+ pers)  in 2 countries. Additionally Marijn has been active as visiting professor of  Industrial Chemistry at UCR . He taught Master courses on Coatings, Pigments, Colour, Photochemistry and Solar Energy.\nSkills: People management; R&D and Technical Program and Project management, Science policy. Science funding mechanisms. international research and innovation cooperation. Data-Automation, Databases,  Coatings, Paints, Pigments, Dispersions, Colorants, R&D, Photophysics, Photochemistry, Chemistry,\n\nThe combined expertise of light, matter, colour, pigments, materials comes together in Marijn's spare time passion: Photography, (occasionally still does some freelance work)",
